# create-saas: scaffold ownership

Templates ship the **proven** dual-mode defaults (first admin, workspace gate, AppShell chrome, billing split). Downstream apps should spend ~90% of time on **domain**, not gutting these templates.

## Ask / recommend first before

- Removing `requireFirstAdmin` / `requireWorkspace` from default proxy
- Dropping AppShell sidebar / theme / workspace switcher from the template layout
- Changing selfhosted vs saas billing defaults
- Removing `.cursor/rules/saas-kit-protect.mdc` from the app-shell template

## Do

- Keep Product section as **placeholders**; Workspace/Account as real shared surfaces
- Bump version + CHANGELOG when template standards change; pin compatible shell

Domain stubs (`add-domain`) are the right place for customer-specific entities.
